    "recap_headline": "Quinnipiac University",
    "recap_text": "Hamden, Conn. \u2013\nAfter the conclusion of game on was played, the Pioneers kept their bats going as they defeated the Bobcats, 10-4, in game two of the series. With the loss, the Bobcats fell to 4-11 overall and 0-2 in conference play.\nSCORE\nSacred Heart 10, Quinnipiac 4\nRECORDS\nQuinnipiac (4-11, 0-2 MAAC) | Sacred Heart (4-11, 3-2 MAAC)\nWinning Pitcher \u2013 Ryan Parker (1-3)\nLosing Pitcher \u2013\nSam Wright\n(0-2)\nSave \u2013 PJ Rogan (1)\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nAlex Irizarry\ngot the Bobcats on the board first in the bottom half of the opening inning, singling home\nChase Camac\nwith the game's first run.\nThe Pioneers had the immediate response, striking for five runs in their half of the second inning to take a four-run lead.\nQuinnipiac made it a three-run game in the fourth inning as\nCaden Williamson\nscored on a\nMatt Park\ngroundout to third.\nWith the score remaining 5-2 in the sixth inning,\nMatt Park\ncame back to the plate and brought the Bobcats a run closer as he brought\nCaden Williamson\nwith a sacrifice fly.\nSacred Heart responded with four straight runs, pushing their lead to 9-3 as the game went to the bottom half of the eighth inning.\nMatt Park\ndrove in his third run of the game, singling home\nJames Marino\nwith Quinnipiac's fourth run of the game.\nThe Pioneers added another run in the ninth and closed out game two with a 10-4 win over the Bobcats.\nNEWS AND NOTES\nSeven different Bobcats recorded hits in the loss to Sacred Heart.\nMatt Park\nled the offense, recording three RBIs in the loss. Park's season RBI total grew to five in the effort.\nAlex Irizarry\ndrove in his 10\nth\nrun of the season with his RBI single in the first inning.\nThe Bobcats drew seven walks in the loss, while the Pioneers drew just four.\nSam Wright\ngot the start and went 5.0 innings, allowing five earned runs and striking out five.\nON DECK\nThe Bobcats will look to avoid the sweep as they go against the Pioneers on Sunday, March 15\nth\n, with first pitch slated for 1 PM."
